# Quality, Security, and Infrastructure

Complements `.cursor/rules/40-quality-security-git.mdc` (git/commit rules).

Policies: `.ai/policies/quality-and-security.md`

## CI Workflows

| Workflow | File | Purpose |
|----------|------|---------|
| CI | `.github/workflows/ci.yml` | Lint, test, typecheck, Rust gates, commitlint |
| Security | `.github/workflows/security.yml` | gitleaks, cargo audit, trivy |
| Quality | `.github/workflows/quality.yml` | Coverage, k6 smoke, docs structure |

Never mark QA PASS without matching CI command evidence.

## Local Verification

```bash
# Frontend
pnpm format:check && pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test

# Backend
make api-lint && make api-test

# Security (graceful skip if tools missing)
pnpm security:scan

# Performance (requires k6)
pnpm test:performance
```

## Security Scanning

- **gitleaks** — secret detection in repo history
- **trivy** — container and config vulnerability scan
- Wrapper: `scripts/security-scan.mjs` skips missing tools locally; CI uses native actions

Security review triggers: auth, passwords, tokens, transfers, validation, logging, dependencies.

Skill: `.ai/skills/security-review.md`

## Infrastructure

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `docker-compose.yml` | Postgres, API, observability profiles |
| `infra/docker/` | API container build |
| `infra/otel/`, `infra/prometheus/`, `infra/loki/`, `infra/grafana/` | Observability |
| `Makefile` | DB migrate/seed, api-dev, api-test |

Observability skill: `.ai/skills/observability.md`

## Performance Testing

- k6 scripts: `scripts/performance/`
- Runner: `node scripts/performance/run-k6.mjs`
- Skill: `.ai/skills/performance-testing.md`

## Prohibited

- Claiming CI pass without executed commands
- Skipping security review on money/auth changes
- Committing secrets (use `.env` locally, never in git)
- `--no-verify` on commits

## ADRs

Infrastructure and cross-cutting changes require ADRs under `docs/ai/adr/`.
